2. Download the real .deb file

Use this exact wget command. The /download/ part of the URL is the secret sauce that tells GitHub to give you the actual binary file, not the webpage:
Bash

wget https://github.com/fastfetch-cli/fastfetch/releases/latest/download/fastfetch-linux-amd64.deb

3. Install it (The safe way)

Once the download finishes, install it. It is actually better to use apt instead of dpkg for local files because apt will automatically pull in any missing dependencies if needed:
Bash

sudo apt install ./fastfetch-linux-amd64.deb
